column1: Word types: A = adjective, ADV = adverb, F = function word (non-specified), N = noun, NUM = numeral, V = verb.

AoA = Age of Acquisition, new = ratings collected for the present study, MRC = ratings (not specified for word class), available on the MRC Psycholinguistic Database (1997). Oxford: Medical Research Council.

Frequency = logarithm of combined written and spoken count divided by total words in corpus of Celex Database (Baayen, R.H., Piepenbrock, R. & Gulikers, L. (1995). The CELEX Lexical Database [CD ROM]. Philadelphia, PA: Linguistic Data Consortium, University of Pennsylvania).
